Hey team — got the MetalLB VLAN VIP issue sorted out. All 7 LB services (MinIO, Milvus, PostgreSQL) are working now across dev/test/prod VLANs.
Short version: MetalLB was handing out VIPs and answering ARP just fine, but traffic on the bnd0.179x interfaces was getting silently dropped. It ended up being four things stacked on each other — OVN wasn't creating DNAT rules for non-OVS interfaces (fixed with routingViaHost: true), ip_forward was getting reset (fixed with ipForwarding: Global), the policy routing tables were sending DNAT'd packets back out the VLAN gateway instead of into OVN (added the ClusterIP route to tables 100/101/102), and rp_filter was dropping packets from external subnets on the VLAN interfaces (disabled it on bnd0.*). Also needed a MASQUERADE rule so OVN can route responses back out the right interface.
